        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 12:17PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 1217 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kuna, or 10 miles southeast of Nampa, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Boise, Meridian, and Kuna around 1220 PM MDT.
Garden City around 1230 PM MDT.
Aldape Summit around 1240 PM MDT.
Lucky Peak Reservoir around 1250 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
